There is no in\-app last\-refreshed indicator.
Diagnostic logs: \f[CR]\(ti/.local/share/mail\-sync.log\f[R],
\f[CR]\(ti/Library/Logs/mbsync\-cohs.log\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]Tag staleness caveat.\f[R] meli\(cqs notmuch backend caches
per\-row tag state at query time.
\f[CR]Ctrl+R\f[R] re\-runs the query and surfaces new arrivals, but does
NOT refresh tag chips on already\-listed rows.
Tags applied to existing messages by the post\-new hook, mailcurator, or
label\-sync processes won\(cqt appear in a long\-lived meli session even
after \f[CR]Ctrl+R\f[R].
The \f[CR]email\f[R] launcher mitigates this by \f[CR]pkill\f[R]\-ing
any existing meli before spawning a fresh one \(em the convention is
\f[B]one keypress = one fresh meli\f[R], not \(lqkeep meli open all
day\(rq.
.PP
The launcher also kickstarts both sync agents
(\f[CR]com.user.mail\-sync\f[R] and
\f[CR]com.williamnapier.mbsync\-cohs\f[R] on Mac;
\f[CR]mail\-sync.service\f[R] and \f[CR]mbsync\-cohs.service\f[R] on
Linux) at relaunch time, so a fresh meli sees mail that\(cqs nearly
current rather than up\-to\-5\-min stale\-from\-last\-tick.
The pulls run in parallel with meli init; notmuch indexing is available
by the time you\(cqd next press \f[CR]Ctrl+R\f[R].
.SH READING
\f[CR]Enter\f[R] on a row opens the envelope view.
\f[CR]Up\f[R]/\f[CR]Down\f[R] (NAV layer) scroll the body \(em
\f[CR]i\f[R]/\f[CR]e\f[R] taps don\(cqt fire in the pager for the same
reason as in the listing (see NAVIGATION).
They \f[B]do\f[R] work in the send\-confirmation dialogue and other
modal forms.
\f[CR]Backspace\f[R] returns to the listing.
